Designed by [https://github.com/kyllikki Vincent Sanders] and released under MIT licence, PNG23D is a command line tool allowing to make a 3D file from a PNG image.

Different picture densities define different heights in 3D file generated. All the hard work is to customize source picture, according to PNG23D settings, to get a good printing file.

Many parameters can be set: 3D object size, height levels number, output format –for example an {{Path|.stl}} file to be printed, or a {{Path|.scad}} one to be edited in [http://www.openscad.org/ OpenScad] ({{Package|media-gfx/openscad}}), etc.

